   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="chapter" xml:id="S1">
            <head>Chapter 1. <locus from="1" to="8"/></head>
            <!--ebb: 2015-08-05: Okay, we have to use <p> as the base structural unit of any prose text in TEI, 
               so we'll have to make each chapter be a single long paragraph in Montalvo. 
               We'll use the <milestone/> element in the Southey text to indicate his imposed paragraph breaks within that.
            A <milestone/> element appears at the beginning of each of Southey's paragraphs.
            -->
            <!--ebb: 2015-08-20: I'm now rethinking this use of milestone, since we've discovered occasional paragraph breaks within chapters in Montalvo. I'm just going to wrap paragraphs in the <p> element the way the TEI intended! 
                  Perhaps the <s> elements and <cl> elements don't really need to be sitting in the same hierarchical positions in the file anyway, since we are using <milestone/> markers to stitch the Southey together with units of the Montalvo text.-->
            <p>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c1"/>Not many years after the passion of our
                     Redeemer<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c2"/>there was a Christian King in the lesser
                  Britain, by name <persName ref="#Garinter">Garinter</persName>,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c3"/>who being in the law of truth, was of much
                  devotion and good ways.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c4"/>This King had two Daughters by a noble Lady
                  his wife.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c5"/>The eldest was married to <persName
                     ref="#Languines">Languines King of Scotland</persName>; she was called
                     <persName ref="#Guirnalda">the Lady of the Garland</persName>,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c6_1"/>because her husband<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c7"/>taking great pleasure to behold her
                  beautiful tresses,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c6_2"/>would have them covered only with a chaplet
                  of flowers.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c8"/><persName ref="#Agrajes">Agrayes</persName>
                  and <persName ref="#Mabilia">Mabilia</persName> were their children,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c9"/>a Knight and Damsel of whom in this history
                  much mention is made.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c10"/><persName ref="#Helisena"
                     >Elisena</persName> the other daughter was far more beautiful,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c11"/>and although she had been demanded in
                  marriage by many great Princes,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c12"/>yet she would wed with none, but for her
                  solitary and holy life was commonly called the Lost Devotee <note anchored="true"
                     resp="#Southey">La Beata perdida. <hi rend="italic">Methodist, Puritan,</hi> or
                        <hi rend="italic">the Elect,</hi> would perhaps express the meaning of <hi
                        rend="italic">Beata,</hi> which is in common use, if they were not sectarian
                     words.</note><anchor ana="end"/><anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c13"/>,
                  because it was considered that for one of such rank,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c14"/>gifted with such beauty<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c15"/>and sought in marriage by so many
                     chiefs,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c16"/>this way of life was not fitting.<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
               </s>
            </p>
            <p>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c17"/>King Garinter who was somewhat striken in
                     years,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c18"/>took delight in hunting.<anchor ana="end"
                  />
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c19"/>It happened one day, that having gone from
                  his town of <placeName ref="#Alima">Alima</placeName><anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>to the chace,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c20"/>and being separated<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c21"/>from his people, as he went along the
                  forest saying his prayers,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c22"/>he saw to the left a brave battle of one
                  Knight against two.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c23"/>Soon had he knowledge of the twain, in
                  that they were his own vassals,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c24"/>who being proud men<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c25"/>and of powerful lineage had often by their
                  evil customs offended him.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c26"/>Who the third was he knew not, but not
                  relying so much in the worth of the one, as he feared the two,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c27"/>he drew aside and waited the event,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>which sorted to such effect,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c28"/>as by the hand of that one the others were
                  both slain.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c29"/>This done <persName ref="#Perion">the
                     Stranger</persName> came towards the King, came towards the King,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c30"/>and seeing him alone, said,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c31"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Perion"/>Gentle Sir, what country is this wherein Knights Errant are
                  thus assailed?<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c32"/>The King replied,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <milestone unit="said" ana="start" resp="#Garinter"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c33_1"/>Marvel not at this, Knight,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c34"/>for our Country yields<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c33_2"/>as others do, both good and bad:<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c35"/>as for these men, they have often
                     offended,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c36"/>even against their Lord and King, who
                  could do no justice upon them, because of their kindred,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c37"/>and also because they harboured in this
                  covered mountain.<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
            </p>
            <p>
               <milestone unit="said" ana="start" resp="#Perion"/>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c39_1"/>This King you speak of,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c38"/>replied <persName ref="#Perion">the
                     Stranger</persName>,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c39_2"/>I come to seek him from a far land,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c40"/>and bring him tidings from a dear
                     friend.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c41"/>If you know where he may be found, I pray
                  you tell me.<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/></s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c42"/>The King answered,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c43"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Garinter"/>Befall what may, I shall not fail to speak what is
                     true.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c44"/>I am the King.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <milestone unit="said" ana="end"/>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c45"/>The Knight then loosing his shield and
                  helmet gave them to his Squire, and went to embrace Garinter, saying that he was
                  King Perion of Gaul who had long desired to know him.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c46"/>Greatly were these Kings contented that
                  their meeting was in such a manner,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c47"/>and conferring together they took their
                     way<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>through the wood towards the city,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c48"/>when suddenly a Hart ran before them
                     which<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>had escaped the toils.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c49"/>They followed at full speed, thinking to
                  kill it,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c50"/>but a Lion springing from a thicket before
                  them, seized the Hart,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c51"/>and having torn it open with his mighty
                     claws,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c52"/>stood fiercely looking at the
                     Kings.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c54"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Perion"/>Fierce as you are<milestone unit="said" ana="intStart"
                     />,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c53"/>said King Perion,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c54_1"/><milestone unit="said" ana="intEnd"/> you
                  shall leave us part of the game!<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c55"/>and he took his arms and alighted from his
                     horse,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c56"/>who being affrighted at the wild beast
                  would not go near him, and placing his shield before him<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c57"/>went towards the Lion sword in
                     hand.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c59"/>The Lion left his prey and came against
                     him,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c60"/>they closed,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>and Perion<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c60_2"/>at the moment when he was under the
                     beast and in most danger,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c61"/>thrust his sword into his belly.<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>When Garinter saw him fall,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c62"/>he said within himself<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c63"/>not without cause is that Knight famed to
                  be the best in the world.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>Meanwhile<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c64"/>their train came up, and then was their
                  prey and venison laid on two horses<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c65"/>and carried to the City.<anchor ana="end"
                  />
               </s>
            </p>
            <p>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c66"/>The Queen being advised of her
                     guest<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c68_2"/>they found<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c67"/>the palace richly adorned,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c68_1"/>and the tables covered.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c69"/>At the highest the Kings seated
                     themselves:<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c70"/>at the other sate the Queen with Elisena
                  her daughter,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c71"/>and there were they served, as in the
                  house of such a man beseemed.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c72"/>Then being in that solace, as that
                  Princess was so beautiful<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c73"/>and King Perion on his part equal,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c75"/>in that hour and point they so regarded
                  each other, that her great modesty and holy life could not now avail,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c76"/>but that she was taken with great and
                  incurable love;<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c77"/>and the King in like manner,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c78"/>though till then his heart had been
                     free,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c79"/>so that during the meal both the one and
                  the other appeared absent in thought.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c80"/>When the tables were removed, the Queen
                  would depart to her chamber;<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c80.1"/>Elisena rising dropt a ring from her
                  lap, which she had taken off when she wash'd her hands,<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c81"/>and in her confusion of mind
                     forgotten.<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c82"/>She stooped for it<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c83"/>and Perion who was near her<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>stooped also,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c84"/>so that their hands met,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c85"/>and he taking her hand prest it.<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>She<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c86"/>coloured deeply<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c87"/>and thanked the King for his
                     service.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <milestone unit="said" ana="start" resp="#Perion"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c88"/>Ah, Lady, said he,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c89"/>it shall not be the last,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c90"/>for all my life shall be spent in your
                     service.<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
            </p>
            <p>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c91"/>She followed her mother, but so
                     disturbed<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c92"/>that her sight was dizzy,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c93"/>and now not able to endure her
                     feelings<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>she went and<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c94"/>discovered them to the damsel <anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c96"/><persName ref="#Darioleta"
                     >Darioleta</persName><anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c95"/>in whom she confided,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c97"/>and with tears from her eyes and from her
                  heart, besought her to find out if King Perion loved any other woman.<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c100"/>Darioleta suprized at this
                     alteration,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c101"/>pitied and comforted her mistress,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c106"/>and went to King Perion's chamber.<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c107_1"/>She found his <persName ref="#Squire1"
                     >Squire</persName> at the door with the King's garments which he was about to
                  give him;<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c108_1"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Darioleta"/>friend<milestone unit="said" ana="intStart"/>,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c107_2"/>said she<milestone unit="said"
                     ana="intEnd"/>,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c108_2"/>go you about your other affairs,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c109"/>for I must wait upon your
                     master<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>.</s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c110"/>The Squire, thinking it was the custom of the country, gave her the garments<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c111"/>and went away.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c112"/>She then entered the chamber where the
                  King was in bed.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c113"/>He, who had seen her converse with
                     Elisena<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c114"/>confidently, now hoped that she might
                  bring some remedy to his passion,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c115"/>and said to her all in trembling,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c116"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Perion"/>fair friend, what demand ye?<milestone unit="said" ana="end"
                     /><anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s><anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c117"/>
                  <milestone unit="said" ana="start" resp="#Darioleta"/>I bring you wherewith to
                  cloathe yourself<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/>, she replied.<anchor ana="end"
                  />
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c118"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Perion"/>That should be for my heart<milestone unit="said"
                     ana="intStart"/>, said Perion, <milestone unit="said" ana="intEnd"/><anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c119"/>which is now stript and naked of all my
                     joy<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>.</s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c120"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Darioleta"/>As how?<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/> said the
                     Damsel.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c121"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Perion"/>Thus<milestone unit="said" ana="intStart"/>, quoth
                     he,<milestone unit="said" ana="intEnd"/> coming into this land with entire
                     liberty,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c122"/>and apprehending nothing but the chance
                  of arms, here in this house I have been wounded by a mortal wound,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c123"/>for which if you fair Damsel, can procure
                  me remedy,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c124"/>you shall be well recompensed<milestone
                     unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>.</s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="report" corresp="#M0_p1_c126"/>He then charged her not to
                  discover him<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="report" corresp="#M0_p1_c127"/>but where it was
                     requisite,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="report" corresp="#M0_p1_c133"/>and told her his love for
                     Elisena.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c139"/>Then said Darioleta, <milestone
                     unit="said" ana="start" resp="#Darioleta"/>my Lord, promise me on the faith of
                  a King and a Knight,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c140"/>that you will take to wife my Lady
                  Elisena, when time shall serve,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c141"/>and right soon will I bring ye, where not
                  only your heart shall be satisfied,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c142"/>but hers also, who, it may be, is in as
                  much or more thought and dolour than you, with the same wound.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c143"/>But without<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>this promise<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c144"/>you shall never win her.<anchor ana="end"
                  />
               </s>
               <milestone unit="said" ana="end"/>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c146"/>The King whose will was already disposed
                  by God<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c147"/>that that which ensued might come to
                     pass,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c148"/>took his sword which was by him,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c149"/>and laying his right hand upon the cross
                  of its hilt, pronounced these words,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c150"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Perion"/>I swear by this Cross, and this Sword wherewith I received the
                  order of Knighthood, to perform whatever you shall require<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c151"/>for the Lady Elisena<milestone
                     unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>.</s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c152"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Darioleta"/>Be you then of good cheer<milestone unit="said"
                     ana="intStart"/>, said she, <milestone unit="said" ana="intEnd"/><anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c153"/>for I also will effect my
                     promise<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>.</s>
            </p>
            <p>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c154"/>Darioleta returned to the Princess<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c155"/>and told her how she had sped;<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <milestone unit="said" ana="start" resp="#Darioleta"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c160_1"/>you know,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c159"/>said she,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c160_2"/>that in the chamber where King Perion
                  lodgeth there is a door opening to the garden,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c161"/>whence your father used to go out,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c162"/>and which at this present is covered with
                  the hangings;<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c163"/>but I have the key thereof,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c166"/>and we can go in<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c165"/>at night, when all in the palace are at
                     rest<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>.</s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c168"/>When Elisena heard this she was highly
                     contented,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c169"/>but recollecting herself, she
                     replied,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c171"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Helisena"/>how shall this be brought to pass,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c172"/>seeing that my father will lodge in the
                  chamber with King Perion?<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c174"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Darioleta"/>Leave that to me <milestone unit="said" ana="end"/>said the
                     Damsel,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c175"/>and with that they parted.<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
               </s>
            </p>
            <p>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c177"/>When it was night Darioleta drew aside
                  the <persName ref="#Squire1">Squire of Perion</persName>, and asked him<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="report" corresp="#M0_p1_c178"/>if he was of gentle
                     birth.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c179"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Squire1"/>Aye, <milestone unit="said" ana="intStart"/>said he,<milestone
                     unit="said" ana="intEnd"/><anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c180"/>the son of a Knight!<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c181"/>but why ask ye?<milestone unit="said"
                     ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c183_1"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Darioleta"/>for the desire I have,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c182"/>quoth she,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c183_2"/>to know one thing,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c184"/>which I beseech you by the faith you owe
                  to God and to the King your master,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>not to hide from me.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c192"/>Who is the Lady whom your Master loveth
                     best?<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <milestone unit="said" ana="end"/>
               <s><anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c193"/>
                  <milestone unit="said" ana="start" resp="#Squire1"/>My Master<milestone
                     unit="said" ana="intStart"/>, replied the Squire, <milestone unit="said"
                     ana="intEnd"/>loves all in general,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c194"/>and none as you mean<milestone
                     unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>.</s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c195"/>While they thus talked Garinter came
                     nigh,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c196"/>who seeing Darioleta in conference with
                  Perion's Squire,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c197"/>called her and asked<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="report" corresp="#M0_p1_c198"/>what he had to say to
                     her.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c199"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Darioleta"/>In sooth my Lord,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/><milestone unit="said" ana="intStart"/>quoth she,
                     <milestone unit="said" ana="intEnd"/><anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c202"/>he tells me that his Master<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>is wont to be alone,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c201"/>and certainly I think he will feel
                  himself embarrassed by your company<milestone unit="said" ana="end"/><anchor
                     ana="end"/>.</s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" type="add"/>Garinter hearing that<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c203"/>went to King Perion and said,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c204"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Garinter"/>My Lord I have many affairs to settle, and must rise at the
                  hour of matins,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c205"/>and that you may not be disturbed,<anchor
                     ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c206"/>you had better be alone in your
                     chamber.<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <milestone unit="said" ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c207"/>King Perion replied,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c208"/><milestone unit="said" ana="start"
                     resp="#Perion"/>do as shall seem best to your liking<milestone unit="said"
                     ana="end"/><anchor ana="end"/>.</s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c210"/>Then Garinter understood that Darioleta
                  had told him rightly of his guest's inclination, and ordered his bed to be removed
                  from Perion's apartment.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
               <s>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c212"/>These tidings Darioleta carried to her
                     mistress,<anchor ana="end"/>
                  <anchor ana="start" corresp="#M0_p1_c223"/>and they waited the hour when all should
                  retire to sleep.<anchor ana="end"/>
               </s>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
